<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1262,1400]" box="[151,254,1262,1287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[151,254,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1262,1400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[559,682,1299,1324]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cephala">
<emphasis box="[559,682,1299,1324]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">S. cephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[754,857,1299,1325]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, but without a rectangular spot in space CuA 
<number box="[1388,1394,1315,1327]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
, so that the examination of male genitalia is necessary to ensure definitive identification. This is the first report of the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[350,424,1374,1400]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
